cript\nfunc _play_music(track: String, looped: bool = true) -> void:\n    if music_player == null:\n        return\n    music_player.stop()\n    if track in audio_streams and audio_streams[track]:\n        music_player.stream = audio_streams[track]\n        if \""loop\"" in music_player.stream:\n            music_player.stream.set(\""loop\"", looped)\n        music_player.play()\n```\nDefault `true` preserves existing call sites.\n\n### C. Fix the latent bug at line 3122\nCurrent: `_play_music(\""final\"" if success else \""final\"")` ŌĆö both branches play `music_final`. Both branches say \""final\"". This is a real bug.\n\nReplace with one-shot success/failure sting:\n```gdscript\n_play_music(\""success\"" if success else \""failure\"", false)\n```\nThen schedule transition to `music_report` (looped) after the sting finishes:\n```gdscript\n# After the one-shot sting finishes, switch to report ambient loop.\n# GDScript 4.x: await music_player.finished signal then play report loop.\nawait music_player.finished\n_play_music(\""report\"", true)\n```\nNote: `await` works in non-_process functions. If `_show_night_report` can't await cleanly, use a flag + `_process` check: `var _pending_report_music: bool = true`, and in `_process`:\n```gdscript\nif _pending_report_music and not music_player.playing:\n    _pending_report_music = false\n    _play_music(\""report\"", true)\n```\nPick whichever fits the surrounding code structure.\n\n### D. `_end_night()` (~line 3025) ŌĆö trigger success/failure sting\nAfter the existing `_play_sfx(\""unlock\"" if success else \""fail\"")`, add:\n```gdscript\nif success:\n    _play_music(\""success\"", false)\nelse:\n    _play_music(\""failure\"", false)\n_pending_report_music = true\n```\n\n### E. Final phase (~line 3212-3221) ŌĆö leave `_play_music(\""final\"")` alone\nThat plays `music_final.mp3` for the chapter-complete screen, different from the success/failure stings.\n\n## Deliverable 2 ŌĆö Task 4 wiring: 2 SFX\n\n### A. Extend `Nig